'''Boar-baiting''' is a [[blood sport]] involving the [[Bait (dogs)|baiting]] of [[wild boar]]s.<ref name="Reuters">[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-indonesia-dogfighting/indonesia-governor-cracks-down-on-bloody-dog-boar-fights-idUSKBN1D71ED Reuters: Indonesia governor cracks down on bloody dog-boar fights]</ref><ref name="Express">[https://www.express.co.uk/news/nature/877512/dog-boar-fights-adu-bagong-banned-indonesia-animal-cruelty Express UK: Barbaric DOG v WILD BOAR fights BANNED after being highlighted in Express]</ref><ref name="Independent">[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/indonesia-dog-wild-boar-fights-traditional-sport-calls-to-ban-end-game-a8006981.html Independent: Dog vs wild boar fights in Indonesia prompt calls to end 'traditional' sport]</ref>

Villagers in [[Indonesia]] call the event "adu bagong" translated as boar fighting.<ref name="Reuters" /><ref name="Express" /><ref name="Independent" /> Boar-baiting began in the 1960s, to test hunting dogs against wild boars.<ref name="Reuters" /><ref name="Express" /><ref name="Independent" /> In 2017, an online petition demanding the halt was created by [[animal rights]] organizations and the [[Government of Indonesia]] banned boar-baiting.<ref name="Reuters" /><ref name="Express" /><ref name="Independent" />

