{{Infobox sports league | title = Canadian Basketball League | current_season = 2016–17 | logo =File:Canadian_Basketball_League.png | pixels = 200px | caption = | sport = Basketball | founded = 2014 | folded = | inaugural = 2016–17 | ceo = [[Butch Carter]] | coach of the year = [[Garrett Kelley]] | motto = Development League | Teams = 4 | Country = {{flagu|Canada}} | Continent = [[FIBA Americas]] ([[Americas]]) | Champion = Scarborough Basketball Club | most_champs = | ticket site = {{URL|https://www.cbltickets.com}} | TV = [[YES TV]] | website = {{URL|https://canadianbasketball.com}} }}
The '''Canadian Basketball League''' ('''CBL''') is a professional [[basketball]] minor league based around the [[Greater Toronto Area]] of Southern Ontario. The CBL was founded in July 2014 by former [[NBA]] coach [[Butch Carter]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ottawacitizen.com/sports/basketball/ex-raptors-coach-butch-carter-pushing-a-dream-of-a-new-canadian-basketball-league|title=Ex-Raptors coach Butch Carter pushing a dream of a new Canadian Basketball League|last=|first=|date=12 December 2014|website=Ottawa Citizen|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/business/2015/01/20/butch-carter-pitching-startup-canadian-basketball-league-but-will-he-find-sponsors.html|title=Butch Carter pitching startup Canadian Basketball League, but will he find sponsors?|last=|first=|date=20 January 2015|website=Toronto Star|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/blogs/eh-game/butch-carter-says-canadian-basketball-league-to-start-small--grow-sustainably-204814384-nba.html|title=Butch Carter says Canadian Basketball League to start small, grow sustainably|last=|first=|date=21 May 2015|website=Yahoo Sports Canada|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
==History==
The four founding member teams were Durham United, Hamilton United, Scarborough and Wellington. Teams play a 24-game regular season followed by league playoffs.
The CBL was to begin play for the 2015–16 season with four teams. That plan was put on hold when a home arena could not be secured for the Hamilton franchise.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.therecord.com/sports-story/6243789-carter-s-pro-hoops-league-put-on-ice-this-season/|title=Carter's pro hoops league put on ice this season|last=|first=|date=21 January 2016|website=Waterloo Region Record|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
CBL began their inaugural season in December 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thespec.com/sports-story/7004419-hamilton-united-to-debut-in-new-canadian-basketball-league/|title=Hamilton United to debut in new Canadian Basketball League|last=|first=|date=5 December 2016|website=Hamilton Spectator|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.therecord.com/sports-story/7006492-carter-s-basketball-league-launches-without-waterloo/|title=Carter's basketball league launches without Waterloo|last=|first=|date=6 December 2016|website=Waterloo Region Record|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> Scarborough defeated Wellington 79-75 in the first-ever league game played at the [[Toronto Pan Am Sports Centre]] on December 18, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.guelphmercury.com/sports-story/7019728-canadian-basketball-league-excited-for-tip-off-in-guelph/|title=Canadian Basketball League excited for tip-off in Guelph|last=|first=|date=14 December 2016|website=Guelph Mercury Tribune|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.insidetoronto.com/photogallerypopup/7035802|title=First-ever Canadian Basketball League game|last=|first=|date=19 December 2016|website=Inside Toronto|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
